  "notes": "ford.com consumer site. Mustang variants (Dark Horse, GTD, Mach-E Rally) share the /mustang/ tree with sub-pages. F-150 specialty variants (Raptor, Raptor R) live under /trucks/f150/. Super Duty variants (F-250/350/450) live under /super-duty/. Session B (2026-05-14): site migrated variant sub-pages from /models/<full-name> to /models/<short-name> (dark-horse, raptor, rally, etc.); mustang-gtd moved to /performance/mustang-gtd/; escape moved to /suvs-crossovers/escape/; Super Duty series pages are now /trucks/super-duty/<series>/ (Ford serves a shared Super Duty template for f-250/f-350/f-450, all return 200). f-150-raptor-r has no dedicated consumer page — Ford covers Raptor R content on the F-150 Raptor page, so it points there. Adopted canonical trailing-slash URLs throughout. Session 6 (2026-05-14, phase-C-bis): added filename-code slug variants — ford.com asset filenames use internal product codes (MST=Mustang, MME=Mustang Mach-E, BRO=Bronco, BRS/BROS/broncosport=Bronco Sport, FSD=Ford Super Duty, F15=F-150 abbreviated, dhsc=Dark Horse SC, MachE concatenated). The catalogs' default slug_variants (e.g. f-150, f150) only match filenames where the model name appears with separators, missing the abbreviated codes Ford uses on most asset filenames. Cross-model collisions vetted: BRO does not match BRS/BROS (different chars after BR), bronco does not match broncosport (no boundary after `bronco`), f15 does not match f150 (no boundary after 15 in `F150`), dhsc does not match dark-horse (different chars).",
